{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"toefl-sentences","unitId":"sentence-055","title":"Sentence 55","sectionId":"sentences-051","sectionTitle":"Sentence 51-60","pageStart":363,"pageEnd":368,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":46,"duplicateEntryCount":9,"pages":[{"number":363,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Sentence 55"},{"type":"text","text":"So musical instruments evolved in ways that optimize their"},{"type":"text","text":"acoustical properties—how the instrument vibrates and sends those"},{"type":"text","text":"vibration through the air to our eardrums."},{"type":"text","text":"因此乐器的演变方式就是优化它们的声学特性，即乐器如何振"},{"type":"text","text":"动，以及如何将所产生的振动通过空气传到我们的耳膜。"},{"type":"section","text":"语法笔记"},{"type":"text","text":"本句主干是“Musical instruments evolved in ways that ...”。句中that"},{"type":"text","text":"引导的定语从句修饰ways，how引导的同位语从句解释说明acoustical"},{"type":"text","text":"properties。"},{"type":"section","text":"核心词表"}]},{"number":364,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"acoustical /əˈkuːstɪkl/ a. 声音的；听觉的","headword":"acoustical"},{"type":"note","text":"同根 acoustics n. 传声效果；音响效果"},{"type":"entry","text":"vibrate /ˈvaɪbreɪt/ v. （使）颤动，（使）振动","headword":"vibrate"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 vibr（摇摆）+ate（使…）→（使）颤动，（使）振动"},{"type":"entry","text":"eardrum /ˈɪrdrʌm/ n. 耳膜；鼓膜","headword":"eardrum"},{"type":"note","text":"记忆 ear（耳朵）+drum（鼓）→击鼓震得耳膜都疼了→耳膜"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 a perforated eardrum 鼓膜穿孔"},{"type":"section","text":"主题归纳"}]},{"number":365,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"常见乐器："},{"type":"entry","text":"accordion /əˈkɔːrdiən/ n. 手风琴","headword":"accordion"},{"type":"entry","text":"bass /beɪs/ n. 贝司","headword":"bass"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 bass drum大鼓"},{"type":"entry","text":"bassoon /bəˈsuːn/ n. 大管","headword":"bassoon"},{"type":"entry","text":"celesta /səˈlestə/ n. 钢片琴","headword":"celesta"},{"type":"entry","text":"cello /ˈtʃeloʊ/ n. 大提琴","headword":"cello"},{"type":"note","text":"搭配 a cello solo 大提琴独奏"},{"type":"text","text":"Chinese lute 琵琶"},{"type":"entry"